'''''Billa''''' ([[2007 in film|2007]]) is a forthcoming high budget [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[film]] directed by [[Vishnuvardhan (director)|Vishnuvardhan]]<ref name="dhoolm">{{cite web| title=''Ajith to do Billa''| work=[http://www.indiaglitz.com Indiaglitz]|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/27441.html |accessdate=28 December|accessyear=2006}}</ref>. The film is produced by [[L.Suresh]]<ref name="dhooim">{{cite web| title=''Back with a bang''| work=[http://www.tamilguardian.com Tamil Guardian]|url=http://www.tamilguardian.com/article.asp?articleid=1006 |accessdate=28 December|accessyear=2006}}</ref> , son of Balaji. His father produced the film, ''[[Billa (1980 film)|Billa]]'' which this is a remake of the [[Rajinikanth]] starrer ''Billa'' which was a remake of the Hindi film, ''[[Don (film)|Don]]''. [[Ajith Kumar]], [[Nayanthara]] and [[Shriya Saran]]<ref name="dhooom">{{cite web| title=''Billa 2007- Shriya and Trisha vie for spots''| work=[http://www.behindwoods.com Behindwoods]|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/dec-06-04/28-12-06-ajith.html|accessdate=28 December|accessyear=2006}}</ref> are the only confirmed cast as yet. [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] is set to compose the music for this film and a couple of old numbers are going to be remixed. The film is set for release in late [[2007]] or early [[2008]]. Shooting will start after Ajith Kumar's next projects, ''[[Aalwar]]'' and ''[[Kireedam (2007 film)|Kireedom]]'' are completed and when Vishnuvardhan's ''[[Sarvam]]'' has been completed . 

==Plot Synopsis==
{{spoiler}}[[Image:Billaaa2006.JPG|thumb|250px|right|[[Ajith]], [[Shriya]] and [[Nayanthara]] in the cast]][[Image:Ajith-rajini-400.jpg|thumb|150px|right|The old 'Billa' [[Rajinikanth]] with the new 'Billa' [[Ajith Kumar]]]]
In [[2007]], the drug trade is booming. The [[Malaysian]] [[Intelligence]] and Anti-Narcotic Department are called upon for assistance by their [[Indian]] counterparts. There are rumours that a drug gang has recently moved their headquarters to [[Kuala Lumpur]].

Billa ([[Ajith Kumar]]) is the leader of an underworld gang until the police commissioner tracks him down and kills him. Then police commissioner tracks down a lookalike of Billa who impersonates Billa to take down the rest of Billa's gang while the police commissioner promises him that he will give a proper [[education]] to the children that he is looking after. But in an unexpected turn of events the [[police commissioner]] dies. 

The police commissioner is the only one who knows the truth about our impersonator who now finds himself in a life-threatening situation - hunted by both the cops and the real Billa's henchmen and to make matters worse, he then finds out that Interpol Officer is a crook and has taken the place of the real person. He is the one responsible for the police commissioner's murder. It's now a race to retrieve a the police commissioner's diary in which the police commissioner has documented his substitution of the real Billa.

